= Contributions

This work contributes the following outcomes:

- A structured attack taxonomy for LLM application security across prompt, retrieval, tool, data, and operational layers.
- A defense-in-depth control model tailored to AI-native attack paths.
- An integrated lifecycle architecture (TSLL) that connects red-team findings to blue-team implementation and monitoring.
- A practical measurement approach using operational security KPIs for continuous assurance.
- A reusable paper structure that can support future case-study extension and empirical validation.

These contributions bridge the implementation gap between threat-driven testing and control-driven governance highlighted in current standards and security engineering guidance @nist_sp800_218_2022 @nist_sp800_53_2020 @nist_sp800_53a_2022.
